East London has been hard hit by heavy rain and this is likely to continue. Heavy rains have caused flooding to many homes in informal settlements. eNCA speaks to Buffalo City Mayor Xola Pakati for more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Mop-up operations are underway in Buffalo City following heavy rains in the area. Heavy rains caused flooding to many homes in informal settlements. Emergency teams have been deployed to assist those who are most at risk. READ: Eastern Cape Floods | Buffalo City residents affected by heavy rains Several people have been reported dead in the Eastern Cape province following torrential rains. "We are now engaged in the mop-up operations, working with the Gift of the Givers and the provincial government to clear the area," said Buffalo City Mayor Xola Pakati. "We have to this end recorded five fatalities, including one person who could not be accounted for so we are worried that that person could be one of the statistics."